      {
        "id": "note_kling_3",
        "type": "utility.note",
        "position": {
          "x": -560,
          "y": 20
        },
        "fields": {
          "body": "### Kling 3.0 workflows\n\nA starter workflow for the three Kling 3.0 video lanes. Each lane has its own group, prompt, preview node, and save node.\n\n- Kling 3.0 text to video creates a video from a written scene prompt.\n- Kling 3.0 image to video animates a start frame. An end frame can be added when you want the video to land on a specific final image.\n- Kling 3.0 motion control uses a reference image plus a driving video to guide the generated motion.\n\nRight-click a group title to enable or mute the list of nodes. Muted nodes cannot be executed during the run this allows you to only run that set of nodes.\n\nImage-to-video and motion-control lanes need source media selected in the Load Image or Load Video nodes before running.\n\n- [Star Media Studio on GitHub](https://github.com/gateway/media-studio)\n- [GitHub issues](https://github.com/gateway/media-studio/issues)\n- [Model credits](https://kie.ai?ref=e7565cf24a7fad4586341a87eaf21e42) \n- [Instagram](https://www.instagram.com/dreamingcomputers/)\n"
        },
        "metadata": {
          "style": {
            "width": 596,
            "height": 658
          },
          "ui": {
            "collapsed": false,
            "advancedExpanded": false,
            "accentColor": "#75a7f5",
            "nodeColor": "#172135",
            "nodeHeaderColor": "#1c2e46",
            "customTitle": "Read Me"
          },
          "execution": {
            "mode": "enabled",
            "cached_run_id": null,
            "cached_artifact_ids": {}
          }
        }
      },
